<h2 id="len"><code class="language-plaintext highlighter-rouge">len</code></h2>

<p>O comando <code class="language-plaintext highlighter-rouge">len()</code> retorna o tamanho de uma lista ou de um string. Um exemplo:</p>
<div class="language-python highlighter-rouge"><div class="highlight"><pre class="highlight"><code><span class="n">s</span> <span class="o">=</span> <span class="s">'EEL/USP'</span>
<span class="n">Ns</span> <span class="o">=</span> <span class="nf">len</span><span class="p">(</span><span class="n">s</span><span class="p">)</span>
<span class="nf">print</span><span class="p">(</span><span class="n">Ns</span><span class="p">)</span>
</code></pre></div></div>
<p>Esse c√≥digo retorna <code class="language-plaintext highlighter-rouge">7</code>, j√° que <code class="language-plaintext highlighter-rouge">'EEL/USP'</code> tem sete caracteres.</p>
